SIMPLE: subordination
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subordination
<hw>Sub*or`di*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>subordination</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
subordinating, placing in a lower order, or subjecting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being subordinate or
inferior to an other; inferiority of rank or dignity;
subjection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Natural creature having a local <qex>subordination</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Holyday.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Place of inferior rank.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Persons who in their several <qex>subordinations</qex> would be
obliged to follow the example of their superiors.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subordinative</ent>⟦br⟧
